pling weight or gain term\\ndocs/coupling_bundle_design.md:185:Milestone 7 uses `nonnegative_delay_ms_per_synapse_or_delay_bin`.\\ndocs/coupling_bundle_design.md:192:  not collapsed to one mean value unless the bundle explicitly declares that\\ndocs/coupling_bundle_design.md:197:Milestone 7 now ships one default kernel-family contract:\\ndocs/coupling_bundle_design.md:208:- the scalar coupling gain stays in the aggregate's signed weight total rather\\ndocs/coupling_bundle_design.md:213:- `point_impulse` is reserved for point-like bundles where each aggregate has\\ndocs/coupling_bundle_design.md:220:Milestone 7 now ships one conservative default delay model:\\ndocs/coupling_bundle_design.md:228:The bundle always records the chosen delay model plus its parameters\\ndocs/coupling_bundle_design.md:233:### Multi-synapse aggregation\\ndocs/coupling_bundle_design.md:235:Milestone 7 uses `sum_over_synapses_preserving_sign_and_delay_bins`.\\ndocs/coupling_bundle_design.md:241:- record at least the aggregated synapse count and total signed weight for each\\ndocs/coupling_bundle_design.md:243:- never cancel excitatory and inhibitory synapses into one unlabeled total\\ndocs/coupling_bundle_design.md:252:- the local synapse registry is the auditable row-level source for every anchor\\ndocs/coupling_bundle_design.md:253:  map and edge bundle\\ndocs/coupling_bundle_design.md:254:- root-local anchor maps and edge bundles refer to the same root IDs and the\\ndocs/coupling_bundle_design.md:259:- a bundle that distributes one coupling event over multiple anchors must state\\ndocs/coupling_bundle_design.md:260:  its normalization convention explicitly in the bundle metadata\\ndocs/coupling_bundle_design.md:264:  as a silent omission from the coupling bundle\\ndocs/coupling_bundle_design.md:269:delay-model metadata, and cloud-normalization rules. Later Milestone 7 tickets\\ndocs/coupling_bundle_design.md:270:may extend the supported family list or add stricter QA, but they should cite\\